-- Singapore's City Developments in joint $278 mln Japan land purchase
-- By Rachel Armstrong
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 05:56AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Sept 30 (Reuters) - Singapore's second largest property developer City Developments Ltd <CTDM.SI> said on Tuesday it has bought, along with an unnamed U.S. investment company, a piece of freehold land in Tokyo for 30.5 billion yen ($278.21 million).

The 16,815 square metre (18,0995 square foot) plot of land is in Tokyo's Shirokane area and was bought from Japan's Seiko Holdings Corp <6286.T>.